repo.name: microG F-Droid repo
repo.description: This is a repository of microG apps to be used with F-Droid. Applications in this repository are signed official binaries built by the microG Team from the corresponding source code.

apps.description: Providing Play Store services to apps. Required for Play Services clients to connect to Play Services.

microG GmsCore is a FLOSS (Free/Libre Open Source Software) framework to allow applications designed for Google Play Services to run on systems, where Play Services is not available.

As the original Play Services, microG GmsCore allows you to contact certain Google services. These services are not open-source.

This is needed by some older client libraries for cloud-to-device-messaging (C2DM), nowadays called Cloud Messaging (GCM).

It will redirect the request to GmsCore and thus will not work stand-alone.
